Venezuela’s Hugo Chavez Says Results Don’t Mean Cancer Risk Gone

-- B y   J o s e   O r o z c o
-- 
2011-07-24T20:21:32Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-24/venezuela-s-hugo-chavez-says-results-don-t-mean-cancer-risk-gone.html
Venezuela ’s President Hugo Chavez
today said medical tests that showed no cancer don’t mean the
risk of the disease has gone.  Speaking on state television the day after returning from
Cuba, where he underwent chemotherapy treatment, Chavez said the
island’s leader  Fidel Castro  had told him: “You have nothing.”  To contact the reporter on this story:
